    "Html": "<p>Trying to bind SelectedIndex of DataGridComboBoxColumn to an integer property. Works fine&nbsp;if property is a string and the string name matches the&nbsp;item in the ComboBox of&nbsp;course, but values in my case are int's that&nbsp;I would like to select the index. Seems simple enough.&nbsp;It does not appear to bind to an int as nicely as the standard .NET combo box does. I have read the thread on the bool binding, I think it has to be&nbsp;simpler than that, no?</p>\r\n<p>Here is the property:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:'Courier New'\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style=\"color:blue\">public</span> <span style=\"color:blue\">int</span> GainMode</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:'Courier New'\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>{</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:'Courier New'\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style=\"color:blue\">get</span> </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:'Courier New'\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>{</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:'Courier New'\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style=\"color:blue\">return</span> m_iGainMode; </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:'Courier New'\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt;font-family:'Courier New'\"><span style=\"\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb